text: Someone recommended me to play this free game a couple days ago, it looked quite intriguing so I did. Finished it in 3 sittings and it turns out it's one of the most unique and weirdest RPGs I've ever played. Hours after finishing it, I'm still not sure I entirely understand what happened. I'd describe this game as a surreal, horror RPG with an Earthbound, Twin Peaks and French touch. I really wasn't sure at first, but at some point everything clicked and I was addicted. It's the same thing with this battle theme, I quickly went from finding it too unstructured for my liking, to bobbing my head everytime it played. Very recommended!
